optional telemetry, that telemetry will be disclosed in the
Documentation and will be off by default.

7.2 Self-Hosted Operation

The Software is self-hosted by Licensee. Licensor does not access,
process, or store any personal data that Licensee loads into, or
processes using, the Software, except where Licensee voluntarily
provides such data to Licensor (for example in connection with a support
request). Where Licensee processes personal data using the Software,
Licensee is the controller in respect of that data for the purposes of
UK GDPR and equivalent legislation, and Licensor is neither a controller
nor a processor.

7.3 Feedback

Where Licensee voluntarily provides Licensor with feedback, suggestions,
bug reports, ideas, or other information relating to the Software
("Feedback"), Licensee grants Licensor a perpetual, irrevocable,
worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive licence to use, reproduce,
modify, and exploit such Feedback for any purpose, without obligation of
confidentiality or compensation. This section does not apply to
source-code contributions, which are governed by Licensor's Contributor
Licence Agreement (where in force).


